<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1924-09-12T01:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1924-09-12T01:00:00-05:00" n="436" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d436">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">706.6193/21: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The Chargé in China</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bell</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the
                                    <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Peking</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1924-09-12T14:00:00+08:00"><hi rend="italic">September 12,
                                        1924—2 p.m.</hi></date><lb/>[Received September 12—10:47
                                a.m.]</dateline></opener>
                        <p>340. My 333, September 8, 4 p.m. French Minister agreed. We have accepted
                            Karakhan’s note of August 26th, sent him our acknowledgment, and he
                            entered into possession of former Russian Legation noon today. He will
                            not occupy it for two or three weeks as it needs cleaning.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bell</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                </body></text></TEI>